SIMPLE: sleepy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sleepy
<hw>Sleep"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sleepier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sleepiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>sl<?/pig</ets>. See
<er>Sleep</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Drowsy; inclined
to, or overcome by, sleep.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She waked her <qex>sleepy</qex> crew.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tending to induce sleep; soporiferous; somniferous;
<as>as, a <ex>sleepy</ex> drink or potion</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Dull; lazy; heavy; sluggish.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'Tis not <qex>sleepy</qex> business;⟦br⟧
But must be looked to speedily and strongly.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Characterized by an absence of watchfulness; <as>as,
<ex>sleepy</ex> security</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sleepy duck</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the ruddy
duck.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleepyhead</ent>⟦br⟧
